<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1038 </DOCNO><TEXT>Twelve years ago, when oil prices were rapidly escalating, renewable energyattracted a great deal of interest, but achieved little. Today, withoil prices fairly stable, less is heard of renewable energy, but it isbecoming respectable and has attracted commercial interest. The largeamount of effort applied to research in renewable energy compared withthe size of the industry is considered and the need to focus on applyingthe technology and developing the market are discussed. Some suggestionsfor achieving this are presented.</TEXT></DOC>